    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Appointment
    Represents an appointment between a patient and a healthcare provider.
    ClinicManagerController
    This class handles various functionalities related to scheduling and managing appointments, providers, and patient information in a healthcare application.
    ClinicManagerMain
     
    CLL
    A Circular Linked List (CLL) implementation to manage a list of Technicians.
    Date
    This class represents a date with year, month, and day attributes.
    Doctor
    Represents a doctor in the healthcare system, extending the Provider class.
    Imaging
    Represents an imaging appointment which includes details about the date, timeslot, patient, provider, and the specific radiology room used for the imaging.
    List<E>
    This class represents a list of appointments.
    ListMethods<E>
    A utility class that provides methods for working with lists of generic elements, specifically handling appointments, timeslots, and formatting.
    Location
    Represents different locations along with their corresponding counties and zip codes.
    Node
    Represents a node in a linked list that stores a Technician object and a reference to the next node.
    Patient
    Represents a patient in the healthcare system.
    Person
    Represents a person with a profile containing personal information.
    Profile
    Represents a profile containing personal information of a person, including first name, last name, and date of birth.
    Provider
    Represents a provider of healthcare services, such as doctors or technicians.
    Radiology
    Represents the different types of radiology scans.
    Sort
    Provides various sorting functionalities for lists of providers, appointments, and patients.
    Specialty
    Represents the different specialties of technicians with their associated charges.
    Technician
    Represents a technician, which is a type of provider with a specific rate per visit.
    Timeslot
    Represents a time slot in a 12-hour format with hours and minutes.
    Visit
    Represents a completed visit associated with an appointment.
